settings.Reporting.report.CLIENTS_INVOIC:
Evaluation according to 'Payment date': The report shows the value of all payments received per {patientSingular} during the defined period. The date of receipt of payment is used as selection criterion.{br}
{br}
Evaluation according to 'Invoice date': The report shows the value of the payments received per {patientSingular} up to the report generation date. The date the invoice was issued is used as selection criterion.{br}
{br}
The report can be generated by gross (incl. VAT ) and net amounts and the values can be grouped daily, weekly, monthly, quarterly and yearly.

Partial payments: Only the value actually paid is reflected.{br}
{br}
Overpayments: These are shown in full, including the overpaid amount. Furthermore, in the reporting mode ‘by payment date’ the following rule applies: As soon as an overpayment is transferred to a ‘client credit position’, only the amount that has not been transferred (=invoice amount) is shown.{br}
{br}
Open account: Prepayments are shown as 'overpayments' and thus as turnover. If the account has a negative balance, this will be reported as a 'partial payment'.{br}
{br}
Vouchers: Payments from redeeming vouchers are shown on the {patientSingular} who redeemed voucher. Cancellation of vouchers (after expiry) count as turnover and are shown on the {patientSingular} as well. On the other hand, the mere sale of vouchers does not represent turnover and is therefore not visible in this report.{br}
{br}
Reminder fees: if an invoice has included reminder fee, the value is also taken into account (if paid).

settings.Reporting.report.INVOICES.speci:
Partial payments: These are displayed as part of the incoming payment. Differences to the invoice amount are shown separately in the report.{br}
{br}
Overpayments: These are shown in full on the invoice belonging to the payment. As soon as an overpayment is transferred to another invoice or a customer credit, it disappears is no longer reported under the original invoice. Differences to the invoice amount are shown in a separate column in the report.{br}
{br}
Open account: Prepayments for current invoices are shown as 'overpayments'. If a current account has a negative balance, it will be reported as a 'partial payment'.{br}
{br}
Vouchers: Payments from redeeming vouchers as well as writing them off (due to expiry) are reported as sales. On the other hand, the mere sale of vouchers does not represent sales and is therefore not visible in this report. A separate table on the report provides information about the current payment status of the relevant vouchers.

