settings.Reporting.report.OPEN.functiona:
The report lists all open positions (i.e. unpaid or partly unpaid invoices, outstanding amounts). This also includes invoices from the creation of vouchers. Invoices that are partially paid are listed on the open item list until they are paid in full.{br}
{br}
The report shows the incoming payments (gross / net) as well as the invoice amounts. It can be filtered by particular status of invoice: issued, reminder 1, 2, 3, or all.

settings.Reporting.report.TREATMENTS_SPL:
Evaluated according to 'Payment date': The report shows the value of the payments received in the period for each tariff/service position. The date of receipt of payment is used as selection criterion.{br}
{br}
Evaluated according to 'Invoice date': The report shows the value of the payments received at the date of report generation for each tariff/service position. The date the invoice was created is used as selection criterion.{br}
{br}
The report includes gross (incl. VAT ) and net amounts. In multi-therapist practices, a separate detailed evaluation is created for each service provider.

Partial payments: These are allocated to the individual tariff/service positions with equal weighting based on the percentage of the partial payment.{br}
{br}
Overpayments: These are shown on the corresponding tariff/service position up to the invoice amount. The amount of the overpayment (i.e. the amount larger than the invoice amount) is shown separately as 'overpayment'. As soon as an overpayment is transferred to another invoice or a client credit position (if recorded in selected period in ‘Payment date’ mode), the separately reported overpayment disappears.{br}
{br}
Open account: Prepayments for current accounts are shown as 'overpayments'. If a current account has a negative balance, it will be reported as a 'partial payment'.{br}
{br}
Vouchers: Payments from redeeming vouchers are shown on the tariff/service positions. Cancellations of vouchers (after expiry) count as turnover and are shown separately in the report. On the other hand, the mere sale of vouchers does not represent turnover and is therefore not visible in this report.

